Patch summary:
Make the Cuttlefish AIDL capture path use ALSA as its only real-time pacing
source.

The primary HAL's emulator workaround skips a transfer whenever the stream
falls behind wall clock. On input, that skips the real ALSA read and returns
zero-filled buffers to AudioRecord.

StreamAlsa also enables MonoPipe's blocking-writer throttle for input even
though ALSA capture reads are already hardware paced. The extra delay makes
the worker progressively fall behind until virtio-snd returns EIO. Conversely,
the client-facing read is non-blocking and substitutes silence whenever the
worker has not filled the pipe yet.

Keep the host-buffer workaround limited to playback, remove MonoPipe's second
capture throttle, and wait for complete input data at the client-facing side.
This keeps the ALSA worker draining continuously and gives AudioRecord one
stable, hardware-paced stream.

